#IPM
##Overview
IPM is a portable profiling infrastructure for parallel codes. It provides a low-overhead performance profile of the performance aspects and resource utilization in a parallel program. Communication, computation, and IO are the primary focus. While the design scope targets production computing in HPC centers, IPM has found use in application development, 
performance debugging and parallel computing education. The level of detail is selectable at runtime and presented through a variety of text and web reports.

-やく
IPMは並列コードのためのポータブルなプロファイル環境
並列プログラム中のソース利用と評価の側面のプロファイルを少ないオーバーヘッドで提供
通信，計算，I/Oは第一のフォーカス
IPMはアプリケーション開発と，性能デバッグ，並列処理の教育に使える
詳細レベルはランタイムに選択でき，選択内容はテキストやwebで公開されている

IPM has extremely low overhead, is scalable and easy to use requiring no source code modification. It runs on Cray XT.s, IBM SP's, most Linux clusters using MPICH/OPENMPI, SGI Altix and the Earth Simulator. IPM is available under an Open Source software license (LGPL). It is currently installed on several Teragrid, Department of Energy, and other supercomputing resources.

-やく
ソースコードの変更なしに用意にプロファイルできて，オーバーヘッドが少ないため，スケーラビリティもある
mpi8ch/openmpiを使用しているほとんどのLinuxクラスタで動く
IPMはオープンソース

IPM brings together several types of information important to developers and users of parallel HPC codes. The information is gathered in a way the tries to minimize the impact on the running code, maintaining a small fixed memory footprint and using minimal amounts of CPU. When the profile is generated the data from individual tasks is aggregated in a scalable way.

-やく
IPCは色んなレベルの情報を取得できる






